LIFE
====

Purpose of this project is to make a useful performance's measurement tool based on the "Game of Life" (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conway%27s_Game_of_Life), suitable on HPC systems.

Target "COMP" activates comp function (much more operations in every cycle).

Compilation - GNU
==================

Serial: gcc life_double_for.c -o life_double_for 

OMP:    gcc life_double_for.c --define OMP --define COMP -fopenmp -o life_double_for_omp 

MPI:    mpicc life_double_for.c --define MPI --define COMP -o life_double_for_mpi

Hybrid: mpicc life_double_for.c --define MPI --define OMP --define COMP -fopenmp -o life_double_for_hybrid

Compilation - INTEL
===================

Serial: icc life_double_for.c -o life_double_for 

OMP:    icc life_double_for.c -O3 -D OMP -D COMP -fopenmp -vec-report -o life_double_for_omp

MPI:    mpicc life_double_for.c -D MPI -D COMP -o life_double_for_mpi

Hybrid: mpicc life_double_for.c -D MPI -D OMP -D COMP -fopenmp -o life_double_for_hybrid

PLEASE NOTE: to compile on MIC use "-mmic" option.

Compilation - PGI
=================
OMP: pgcc -mp=numa life_double_for.c -DOMP -DCOMP -fast -mp -Minfo -o life_double_for_omp

ACC: pgcc life_double_for.c -acc -DCOMP -ta=nvidia,time -Minfo=accel -lpgacc -o life_double_for_acc

~ on nvidia device type 'nvidia-smi -l 1' to monitor GPUs activity

Version History:
================

